# Git Worktrees

Feature work runs in **linked worktrees**, not on the main checkout. Keeps `C:\Users\bruce\3dgame` free for `dev` / quick fixes while features live in parallel folders.

## Layout

| Path | Role |
|------|------|
| `C:\Users\bruce\3dgame` | **Primary checkout** — stay on `dev` (or briefly `main` for release/hotfix). |
| `C:\Users\bruce\3dgame-worktrees\<slug>` | **Feature worktrees** — one folder per branch. |

**Slug:** branch name with `/` → `-` (e.g. `feat/escape-completion` → `feat-escape-completion`).

## Create (new feature)

```powershell
cd C:\Users\bruce\3dgame
git fetch origin
git checkout dev
git pull origin dev
git worktree add -b feat/<name> C:\Users\bruce\3dgame-worktrees\feat-<name> dev
```

Existing branch (must **not** be checked out elsewhere):

```powershell
git worktree add C:\Users\bruce\3dgame-worktrees\feat-<name> feat/<name>
```

Then switch this Cursor agent to the worktree with MCP `move_agent_to_root` (`rootPath` = the worktree path). Open **that** folder in Unity (separate `Library/` — first open reimports).

## Agent defaults

- New `feat/` / `fix/` / `chore/` work → **create or reuse a worktree**; do not pile feature commits onto the primary checkout while it should stay on `dev`.
- After `git worktree add`, call **`move_agent_to_root`** so the chat workspace matches the worktree.
- Same branch cannot be checked out in two worktrees — if add fails, `git worktree list` and free the branch (usually switch primary back to `dev`).
- Branching / PR base rules unchanged: off `dev`, PRs target `dev` (see `git-branching.mdc`).
- Commit/push/playtest gates unchanged (`development-workflow.mdc`).

## Remove (after merge)

```powershell
git worktree remove C:\Users\bruce\3dgame-worktrees\feat-<name>
# or: git worktree remove --force <path>  only if the folder is gone/broken
git branch -d feat/<name>   # after merge; user must ask before delete
```

## Unity notes

- Each worktree is its own project path → own `Library/` / `Temp/` (gitignored). Expect a long first import.
- Playtest the **worktree** project in Unity, not the primary `3dgame` folder, when the branch lives in a worktree.
